Key Match Events: Trae Young hit a game-winning half-court shot to give the Hawks a 124-121 victory.
Collin Sexton tied the game at 121 with a tough 3-pointer just seconds before Trae Young's game-winner.
Trae Young finished with 24 points and 20 assists.
Lauri Markkanen scored 35 points for the Jazz, including eight 3-pointers.
Post-Match Reflections: This win gets the Hawks back above .500 in the middle of a topsy-turvy season.
The Hawks are currently in sixth place in the Eastern Conference through 37 games.
